<html><head><title>SOE Promotes "Reloadable" Credit Cards</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>SOE Promotes "Reloadable" Credit Cards</h3><p>In the olden days, the only way you could get an EQ account was to have access to a credit card.  This limited method kept quite a few people from playing and was a source of frustration, but today that's all changed.<br><br>There are quite a few ways to pay for your game subscriptions today, including:<br><br>Game Pass<br>Debit Card<br>Credit Card<br><br>and now, the "reloadable" credit cards, which are basically a purchasing card without a line of credit.  SOE has posted a <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/news_article.vm?id=50356">detailed explanation</a> of how these cards work and where to purchase them.  There's just no excuse not to play!</div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Saturday, 24 Feb, 2007<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=26867">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=26867</a><br>Printed On: Tue Feb 27 21:27:39 PST 2007<br>©2005 IGN Entertainment</font></span>